---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../../lib/seo/site';

const title = 'Privacy Policy';
const description = 'How Advanced Analytica handles personal data on this website.';

const page = {
  title,
  description,
  url: `${SITE_URL}/legal/privacy`,
  breadcrumbs: [
    { name: 'Home', url: `${SITE_URL}/` },
    { name: 'Privacy', url: `${SITE_URL}/legal/privacy` }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} page={page}>
  <section class="container-narrow py-16">
    <div class="eyebrow">Legal</div>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold text-ink">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="prose mt-6">
      <p><strong>Last updated: 20 April 2026.</strong></p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Advanced Analytica Ltd uses personal
        data in connection with this website, <a href={SITE_URL}>{SITE_URL}</a>.
        It reflects how the site currently operates.
      </p>

      <p>
        This website is primarily a static informational site. We do not
        knowingly use advertising trackers on the site and we do not sell
        personal data.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        For the purposes of applicable data protection law, including the UK
        GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018, the data controller for this
        website is Advanced Analytica Ltd.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you need our registered address, company number, or want to make a
        privacy-related enquiry, please contact us via the <a href="/company/contact"
          >Contact</a
        > page.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on how you use the site, we may process the following
        categories of personal data:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Technical usage data such as IP address, browser type, device
          information, referring URL, and basic request metadata that may be
          captured in standard web server or hosting logs.
        </li>
        <li>
          Information you choose to enter into the contact forms, such as your
          name, email address, company, topic, and message.
        </li>
        <li>
          Information your organisation may share with us through procurement,
          commercial, or project initiation channels.
        </li>
        <li>
          Communications data if you email us or otherwise correspond with us.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How the contact forms work</h2>
      <p>
        The contact forms currently available on this site are designed to
        send your enquiry to Advanced Analytica by email. The site does not
        store enquiry data in a website database operated by us.
      </p>
      <p>
        As currently implemented, form submissions are sent to a small
        serverless endpoint operated as part of our website infrastructure.
        That endpoint validates the submission and passes it to our configured
        email delivery provider so the enquiry can be delivered to Advanced
        Analytica.
      </p>
      <p>
        Information you submit through the forms will be processed by our
        website hosting provider, relevant email delivery infrastructure, and
        by us as part of normal business correspondence.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use personal data</h2>
      <p>We may use personal data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>operate, secure, and maintain the website;</li>
        <li>respond to enquiries, briefing requests, and business communications;</li>
        <li>manage commercial, procurement, and project-related discussions;</li>
        <li>monitor and investigate misuse, security issues, or technical faults;</li>
        <li>comply with legal, regulatory, and contractual obligations;</li>
        <li>establish, exercise, or defend legal claims where necessary.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our lawful bases</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK data protection law, the lawful bases we are most likely to
        rely on for this website are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Legitimate interests</strong>, for running the site securely,
          responding to business enquiries, and managing ordinary website and
          commercial operations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Steps prior to entering into a contract</strong>, where you or
          your organisation contact us about services, procurement, or a
          potential engagement.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal obligation</strong>, where we need to retain or disclose
          information to comply with applicable law or regulation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Consent</strong>, where that is the appropriate basis for a
          specific activity. If we rely on consent, you can withdraw it.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This site may use Google Analytics where it has been enabled and you
        have accepted analytics through the on-site consent control. Analytics
        is not loaded before you accept it.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not use advertising cookies, Meta Pixel, or similar cross-site
        advertising tracking technologies through this site.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        If you accept analytics, Google Analytics may collect technical and
        usage information such as pages viewed, approximate location derived
        from network data, device and browser information, referrer information,
        and interaction events. We use this information to understand which
        content is useful and to improve the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can decline analytics when the consent control is shown. You can
        also reset your choice by clearing this site's local storage in your
        browser.
      </p>

      <h2>Third parties and external services</h2>
      <p>
        This site may involve limited third-party processing where necessary to
        render or operate the site, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Hosting and infrastructure providers, which may process technical log
          data such as IP addresses and request metadata.
        </li>
        <li>
          Google Analytics, where enabled and accepted by you, for website
          usage measurement and improvement.
        </li>
        <li>
          Google Fonts, if loaded from Google-hosted font infrastructure. When
          your browser requests those fonts, Google may receive technical data
          such as your IP address and browser details.
        </li>
        <li>
          Email delivery infrastructure used to route contact form submissions
          and business correspondence.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not permit third parties to use your personal data for their own
        unrelated marketing purposes through this site.
      </p>

      <h2>How long we keep data</h2>
      <p>
        We keep personal data only for as long as reasonably necessary for the
        purpose for which it was collected, including to manage enquiries,
        maintain records of business communications, comply with legal
        obligations, and protect our legal position where required.
      </p>
      <p>
        Retention periods vary depending on the nature of the information and
        the context in which it was provided.
      </p>

      <h2>International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some service providers used in connection with this site may process
        data outside the UK. Where that happens, we expect appropriate
        safeguards to be used in line with applicable data protection law.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take a controlled approach to governance, security, and operational
        change. No internet-based service can be guaranteed to be completely
        secure, but we aim to use proportionate technical and organisational
        measures appropriate to the nature of this website and the information
        involved.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can also review our <a href="/company/security">Security</a> page
        for a high-level summary of our operational posture.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Subject to applicable law, you may have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>request access to personal data we hold about you;</li>
        <li>request correction of inaccurate or incomplete data;</li>
        <li>request deletion of your personal data in certain circumstances;</li>
        <li>object to or request restriction of certain processing;</li>
        <li>request portability of data where that right applies;</li>
        <li>withdraw consent where processing is based on consent;</li>
        <li>
          complain to the UK Information Commissioner’s Office if you believe
          your data has been handled unlawfully.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        This site is intended for business and professional audiences. It is
        not directed at children, and we do not knowingly collect personal data
        from children through the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes
        to the site, legal requirements, or the way we operate. The version
        published on this page is the current version.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how personal data is
        handled in connection with this site, please contact us via the <a
          href="/company/contact">Contact</a
        > page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
